Subject: Re: [VB] pics of my '65 & sound stuff

 


So, are you driving it yet?

 

I bought 100sq ft of Fatmat sound deadening, which looks a lot like the
stuff you used in your EZ camper.

 

This is for my 66 kombi, which is a rattley empty tin box.   I have
installed about half the sound deadening, and not noticed a huge difference
when driving.     It is more that well yes, it might be a bit quieter,
maybe.   See what I mean?    

When I knock on the bus, it does sound more of a thud that a ting ting ting,
though.  

 

 

Oh well, when I get an interior in it I am sure it will be quieter. 

 Finally got the cab roof directional vane seals ordered, can install the
cab roof panels when those are in.
